# Cost control (default)

Unless the user explicitly requests a **go-live audit** (see exception below), follow these rules on every task.

## Model and agents

- Use the cheapest model that can safely complete the task.
- Do not use Opus unless the user says "Use Opus."
- Do not use high-thinking mode unless explicitly requested.
- Do not spawn cloud agents unless explicitly approved.
- Do not run multiple agents in parallel unless explicitly approved.
- Do not invoke Bugbot or security-review unless the user explicitly asks.

## Scope and exploration

- One focused task per turn. If the user lists multiple items, ask which to do first unless they numbered priorities.
- Before editing, list the exact files you plan to touch.
- Read and search only files needed for the current task. Do not scan the whole repo.
- Prefer `@` file/folder references from the user over broad exploration.
- Make the smallest safe change. Do not refactor or redesign outside the request.
- After editing, run only necessary checks (lint/typecheck on changed files, targeted tests).

## When blocked or scope is unclear

- Ask one short clarifying question instead of exploring widely.
- Stop and ask before work that may touch many files, many steps, or high token usage.

## Go-live audit exception

When the user explicitly asks for a **go-live audit**, **launch review**, **whole-app review**, **pre-launch audit**, or similar full-app pass before shipping, the cost limits above are relaxed. In that mode:

- Broader repo exploration and cross-cutting checks are allowed.
- Bugbot and/or security-review may be used if the user wants a formal review.
- Opus or higher-thinking models are allowed only if the user requests them.

For all other work, stay in default cost-control mode even if the task feels large — split it into smaller scoped steps and confirm with the user.
